==nuts== [[check-updates]]  \[Options\]... {{\<ids\>}} ...
       check if a newer version of ==nuts== is available in the current workspace without performing updates
       Take the same arguments and options as [[update]] command
       [[-a]] or [[--all]] : force updates of both workspace\'s api, runtime extensions and installed components
       [[-w]] or [[--ws]] or [[-workspace]] : update all workspace\'s related components (api, runtime and extensions)
       [[-i]] or [[--installed]] : update all installed components
       [[-e]] or [[--extensions]] : update all workspace\'s extensions
       [[-r]] or [[--runtime]] : update workspace\'s runtime component (minor workspace update)
       [[-A]] or [[--api]] : update workspace\'s api (major workspace update)
       [[-v]] {{\<arguments\>}}
       or [[--version]] {{\<version\>}}
            : force updates to the provided {{\<version\>}} (may be a downgrade)
            
@@STANDARD OPTIONS@@ :
    This command supports standard options :
       [[-t]] or [[--trace]] : enable trace operation/result with a meaning message (default true)
       [[--output-format]]=[[props|plain|json]] : define the format to trace operation
       [[--plain]]: trace operation as plain text. equivalent to [[--output-format]]=[[plain]]
       [[--json]]: trace operation as json. equivalent to [[--output-format]]=[[json]]
       [[--xml]]: trace operation xml. equivalent to [[--output-format]]=[[xml]]
       [[--props]]: trace operation as (java) properties, key value list. equivalent to [[--output-format]]=[[props]]
       [[--table]]: trace operation as table. equivalent to [[--output-format]]=[[table]]
       [[--tree]]: trace operation as tree. equivalent to [[--output-format]]=[[tree]]

@@EXAMPLES:@@
        ==nuts== check-updates [[--help]]
            shows this help and exit
       
        ==nuts== check-updates
            check updates for current workspace
